[SN]TITLE[SN]
Crawley Town 0-0 Hartlepool United

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hartlepool moved nine points clear of the bottom two with a battling goalless draw away at mid-table Crawley.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
In a poor first half, Nathan Thomas nearly opened the scoring for Pools but his fierce drive went just wide.
Thomas continued to impress after the break and was unlucky to see his effort powerfully strike the crossbar.
With time running out, Crawley nearly stole the victory against the run of play but Sonny Bradley headed agonisingly wide from three yards out.
