Crawley Town boss Mark Yates told BBC Surrey: "Literally the last kick touch of the ball, you're expecting it from five yards out for the net to bulge and it could have been a bit fortunate to grab the three points.
"But it wasn't to be and probably a draw was a fair result in the end.
"We had to dig in and I wanted to see more in the second half and I thought there was more in the tank."
